      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WAVES OF CHANCE (2) produced a strong effort last time out when he came from this barrier and scored by 3 metres at this venue. Up in distance but has won at the trip before. Should enjoy an economical run so could go back to back. KIMCANDO (7) did some work from a similar barrier but stuck on for second to Waves of Chance last week. Owns a decent record at this longer distance so is chance to turn the tables. NEEDBEE (5) takes a step up in grade but is hard to knock off back-to-back wins. YUKON BE SERIOUS NZ (8) draws wide but has been tackling stronger company of late including back-to-back placings here last month. BUBBY TO BASE (1) has been coming from tougher barriers of late but was a close second here the last time she drew on the pegs.",
